metadata.title: MD Helicopters MD 500
aws::graph::propositions: MD Helicopters MD 500 Variants
MD 500D is a commercial version of the MD Helicopters MD 500.
MD 500D was introduced in 1976.
MD 500D is powered by an Allison 250-C20B engine.
The Allison 250-C20B engine is rated at 420 shp (313 kW).
MD 500D was certified in 1976.
MD 500D is also known as 369D.
MD 500E is an executive version of the MD 500D.
MD 500E features a recontoured nose.
MD 500E was certified in 1982.
MD 500E is also known as 369E.
NH-500E is an Italian-built version of the MD 500E.
NH-500E was license-produced by Breda Nardi.
Breda Nardi produced the NH-500E before merging with Agusta.
MD 520N is a NOTAR version of the MD 500E.
NOTAR stands for NO TAil Rotor.
MD 520N was certified in 1991.
MD 520N is powered by Rolls-Royce 250-C20R/2 engine.
The Rolls-Royce 250-C20R/2 engine was formerly known as Allison 250-C20R/2.
The Rolls-Royce 250-C20R/2 engine is rated at 450 shp.
MD 530F is a hot and high version of the MD 500E.
MD 530F is powered by a Rolls-Royce 250-C30HU engine.
The Rolls-Royce 250-C30HU engine was formerly known as Allison 250-C30HU.
The Rolls-Royce 250-C30HU engine is rated at 650 shp (485 kW).
MD 530F was certified in 1984.
MD 530F is also known as 369F.

text:
MD 500D (369D)
New commercial version from 1976 powered by an Allison 250-C20B rated at 420 shp (313 kW); certified in 1976.
MD 500E (369E)
Executive version of the 500D with recontoured nose; certified in 1982.
NH-500E
Italian-built version of the 500E. License-produced by Breda Nardi before merging with Agusta.
MD 520N
NOTAR (NO TAil Rotor) version of the 500E, certified in 1991. Powered by Rolls-Royce (formerly Allison) 250-C20R/2 rated at 450 shp.
MD 530F (369F)
Hot and high version of the 500E powered by a Rolls-Royce (formerly Allison) 250-C30HU rated at 650 shp (485 kW), certified in 1984.
